news.title: UC Punawale Skyscrapers acquires 2.38 hectare land in Pimpri-Chinchwad for Rs 129 crore
news.para: UC Punawale Skyscrapers paid a stamp duty of Rs 9.03 crore and a registration fee of Rs 30,000, according to the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) documents reviewed by Square Yards.

news.title: FICCI, Assocham seek input tax credit under CGST on commercial properties meant for leasing purposes
news.para: The associations have written letters to the finance ministry and have urged the latter to permit availing of the ITC where the immovable property is constructed for the provision of leasing services.

news.title: Get plots in unauthorised colonies registered by Feb 28: Mohali DC to residents
news.para: She said that as the deadline fixed by the Punjab govt to give relief to plot holders (up to 500 square yards) for registration of their plots in unauthorised colonies was approaching, they should take maximum benefit from the policy.

news.title: Gurugram: 600 buildings in DLF 3 with extensions have two weeks for ‘correction’
news.para: DTCP officials said on Tuesday that the owners of 600 properties were initially issued show-cause notices and could not give satisfactory responses on illegal construction or use of the residential buildings for commercial purposes.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC issues 3,200 notices to property tax defaulters
news.para: This initiative is part of efforts to enhance property tax collection during the current financial year. NDMC aims to collect Rs 1,150 crore from property tax in 2024-25, compared to Rs 1,030 crore collected in 2023-24.

news.title: Mumbai: Illegal structures in Dharavi post-drone survey to be razed
news.para: The NMDPL, the special purpose vehicle set up for the redevelopment of Dharavi, had in Nov last year submitted the Dharavi Development Plan for the 251-hectare Dharavi Notified Area (DNA) to the Maharashtra govt for its consideration.

news.title: Lucknow development body to launch plot registration for Mohan Road Scheme in April
news.para: The scheme's first phase will offer 2,000 plots in Sector 6 and Block 3 through a lottery system. The ambitious project is gaining momentum with the layout plan for Sector 5 already submitted to RERA for approval.

news.title: Bengaluru development body demands withdrawal of illegally issued certificate
news.para: In response, Bettahalasur Gram Panchayat wrote a letter to the BDA Engineering Officer-2 on February 14, 2025, stating that the OC issued for the buildings has been withdrawn, as it has no jurisdiction to issue such an OC or building plan. “The panchayat meeting held on February 3 has approved the withdrawal of the OC,’’ the letter read.

news.title: State may move SC for genuine Dombivli flat buyers: Maharashtra CM
news.para: He said, "If necessary, the state govt will go to the Supreme Court to protect genuine flat buyers." The CM said he was apprised of the situation by local MLA and BJP executive president Ravindra Chavan.

news.title: Madras HC orders demolition of seven unauthorised floors in Pondy Bazar commercial building
news.para: Rejecting the request of the builder to regularise the illegal construction, a division bench of Justice S M Subramaniam and Justice K Rajasekar observed that regularisation of unauthorised construction could not be claimed as an absolute right.

news.title: Bengaluru: Consumer forum orders EXD Projects to refund buyer for failing to deliver flat
news.para: "Customers can't be made to wait indefinitely for possession. Once a sale agreement is executed, it is the duty of the builder to be transparent in their dealings," the consumer court ruled.

news.title: Valor Estate plans business realignment with non-core divestment, hospitality demerger
news.para: The planned divestment includes the sale of stake in dairy processing unit Schreiber Dynamix Dairies, a joint venture between US-based Schreiber Foods and Dynamix Dairy, and a majority stake in Sahyadri Agro and Dairy.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM lays foundation stone for TIDEL parks in Madurai, Tiruchi
news.para: The facility at Tiruchirappalli will come up at an estimated Rs 403 crore at Panjappur over 5.58 lakh sq ft space.

news.title: New home prices in China stagnate in January 2o25 as sector struggles
news.para: Prices were unchanged for the second straight month, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics data. On a year-on-year basis, new home prices fell 5.0%, narrowing a 5.3% drop the previous month.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces and Livingstone Infra to redevelop project in Mahalaxmi, Mumbai
news.para: Amit Kumar Sinha, managing director & CEO of Mahindra Lifespaces said, "This development marks Mahindra Lifespaces’ strategic expansion into South Mumbai’s premium real estate market."

news.title: Ludhiana civic body razes 10 illegal commercial constructions and an illegal colony
news.para: Officials stated that the operation was carried out under the direction of MC commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal and that similar enforcement actions would continue.

news.title: Mohali civic body to conduct drone-powered property tax assessment
news.para: The Mohali civic body will use drones to conduct a survey of the properties for tax assessment as well as to detect property violations in the city.

news.title: Greentown China to issue $150 million additional bonds to refinance debt
news.para: The state-backed property developer last week said it sold $350 million worth of 8.45% senior notes due in 2028, the first dollar bond sale by a Chinese property developer since early 2023, in a sign that some investor appetite for speculative-grade China property debt could be returning.

news.title: Karnataka PWD minister directs officials to stop unauthorised construction on highways
news.para: Over the past two years, the district administration, in coordination with police department, identified black spots with high accident rates. Necessary scientific measures will be taken to prevent further accidents, with priority funding allocated for these projects.
